objectives.name: Primary Objective
objectives.text: The trial will continue until the required number of adjudicated primary endpoint events have occurred to be able to comply with the objective of the trial.

objectives.name: Key Secondary Objectives
objectives.text: To evaluate key secondary endpoints which are part of the testing strategy

objectives.name: Safety Objective
objectives.text: Safety will be evaluated descriptively on the treated set.

endpoints.name: Primary Endpoint
endpoints.text: The composite primary endpoint for this trial is the time to first event of adjudicated CV death or adjudicated HHF in patients with HFrEF.

endpoints.name: Key Secondary Endpoint 1
endpoints.text: Occurrence of adjudicated HHF (first and recurrent)

endpoints.name: Key Secondary Endpoint 2
endpoints.text: eGFR (CKD-EPI)cr slope of change from baseline

endpoints.name: Other Secondary Endpoint 1
endpoints.text: Time to first occurrence of chronic dialysis or renal transplant or sustained reduction of ≥40% eGFR (CKD-EPI)cr or sustained eGFR (CKD-EPI)cr <15 mL/min/1.73 m2 for patients with baseline eGFR ≥30 mL/min/1.73 m2 or sustained eGFR (CKD-EPI)cr <10 mL/min/1.73 m2 for patients with baseline eGFR <30 mL/min/1.73 m2

endpoints.name: Other Secondary Endpoint 5
endpoints.text: Time to onset of diabetes mellitus (DM) in patients with pre-DM

endpoints.name: Other Secondary Endpoint 6
endpoints.text: Change from baseline in clinical summary score (HF symptoms and physical limitations domains) of the KCCQ at week 52

endpoints.name: Other Secondary Endpoint 7
endpoints.text: Occurrence of all-cause hospitalisation (first and recurrent)

endpoints.name: Safety Criterion 3
endpoints.text: Incidence and intensity of AE including serious AE (SAE)

endpoints.name: Safety Criterion 4
endpoints.text: Withdrawal from trial medication due to AE

endpoints.name: Safety Criterion 5
endpoints.text: Clinically relevant new finding or worsening of existing condition on physical examination

endpoints.name: Safety Criterion 6
endpoints.text: Clinically relevant changes in laboratory measurements from baseline

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Age requirement
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Age ≥18 years at screening. For Japan only: Age ≥ 20 years at screening

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Sex and Contraception
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Male or female patients. WOCBP must be ready and able to use highly effective methods of birth control per ICH M3 (R2) [R09-1400] that result in a low failure rate of less than 1% per year when used consistently and correctly. A list of contraception methods meeting these criteria is provided in the patient information

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Chronic HF Diagnosis
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Patients with chronic HF diagnosed for at least 3 months before Visit 1, and currently in HF NYHA class II-IV

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: LVEF Requirement
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Chronic HF with reduced EF defined as LVEF ≤ 40% per local reading (obtained under stable condition by echocardiography, radionuclide ventriculography, invasive angiography, MRI or CT). A historical LVEF may be used if it was measured within 6 months prior to visit 1 or the LVEF may be measured after study consent has been obtained. The LVEF must be documented in an official report prior to randomization.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: HF Evidence and NT-proBNP
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: In addition to LVEF ≤40%, patients must have at least one of the following evidence of HF: a) If EF ≥36% to ≤40%: Elevated NT-proBNP at Visit 1 ≥2500 pg/ml for patients without AF, OR ≥5000 pg/ml for patients with AF, analysed at the Central Laboratory, b) If EF ≥31% to ≤35%: Elevated NT-proBNP at Visit 1 ≥1000 pg/ml for patients without AF, OR ≥2000 pg/ml for patients with AF, analysed at the Central Laboratory, c) If EF≤30%: Elevated NT-proBNP at Visit 1 ≥600 pg/ml for patients without AF, OR ≥1200 pg/ml for patients with AF, analysed at the Central Laboratory d) For EF ≤ 40% and documented HHF within 12 months prior to visit 1, elevated NT-proBNP at Visit 1 ≥600 pg/ml for patients without AF and ≥ 1200 pg/ml for patients with AF, analysed at the Central Laboratory.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Medical Therapy for HF
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Appropriate dose of medical therapy for HF (such as ACEi, ARB, β-blocker, oral diuretics, MRA, ARNI, ivabradine) consistent with prevailing local and international CV guidelines, stable for at least 1 week prior to Visit 1 and during screening period until Visit 2 (Randomisation) with the exception of diuretics stable for only one week prior to Visit 2 to control symptoms. The investigator must document in the source documents the reason why patient not on target dose per local guidelines

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Medical Devices
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Appropriate use of medical devices such as cardioverter defibrillator (ICD) or a cardiac resynchronization therapy (CRT) consistent with prevailing local or international CV guidelines (refer also to exclusion #29)

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: BMI Requirement
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Body Mass Index (BMI) < 45 kg/m2 at Visit 1 (Screening)

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Informed Consent
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Signed and dated written ICF in accordance with Good Clinical Practice (GCP) and local legislation prior to admission to the trial

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Recent CV Events
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Myocardial infarction (increase in cardiac enzymes in combination with symptoms of ischaemia or newly developed ischaemic ECG changes), coronary artery bypass graft surgery, or other major cardiovascular surgery, stroke or TIA in past 90 days prior to Visit 1

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Heart Transplant
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Heart transplant recipient, or listed for heart transplant

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: LVAD
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Currently implanted left ventricular assist device (LVAD)

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Specific Cardiomyopathies
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Cardiomyopathy based on infiltrative diseases (e.g. amyloidosis), accumulation diseases (e.g. haemochromatosis, Fabry disease), muscular dystrophies, cardiomyopathy with reversible causes (e.g. stress cardiomyopathy), hypertrophic obstructive cardiomyopathy or known pericardial constriction

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Valvular Heart Disease
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Any severe (obstructive or regurgitant) valvular heart disease, expected to lead to surgery during the trial in the investigator’s opinion

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Acute Decompensated HF
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Acute decompensated HF (exacerbation of chronic HF) requiring i.v. diuretics, i.v. inotropes, or i.v. vasodilators, or LVAD within 1 week from discharge to Visit 1 (Screening) and during screening period until Visit 2 (Randomisation)

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Atrial Fibrillation/Flutter
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Atrial fibrillation or atrial flutter with a resting heart rate >110 bpm documented by ECG at Visit 1(Screening)

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Ventricular Arrhythmia
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Untreated ventricular arrhythmia with syncope in patients without ICD documented within the 3 months prior to Visit 1

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Chemotherapy/Peripartum Cardiomyopathy
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Diagnosis of cardiomyopathy induced by chemotherapy or peripartum within the 12 months prior to Visit 1

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Bradycardia/Heart Block
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Symptomatic bradycardia or second or third degree heart block without a pacemaker after adjusting beta-blocker therapy, if appropriate

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: High Blood Pressure
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Systolic blood pressure (SBP) ≥ 180 mmHg at Visit 2. If SBP >150mmHg and <180mmHg at Visit 2, the patient should be receiving at least 3 antihypertensive drugs

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Hypotension
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Symptomatic hypotension and/or a SBP < 100 mmHg at Visit 1 or Visit 2

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Pulmonary Disease
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Chronic pulmonary disease requiring home oxygen, oral steroid therapy or hospitalisation for exacerbation within 12 months, or significant chronic pulmonary disease in the opinion of the investigator, or primary pulmonary arterial hypertension

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Liver Disease
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Indication of liver disease, defined by serum levels of either ALT (SGPT), AST (SGOT), or alkaline phosphatase above 3 x upper limit of normal (ULN) as determined at Visit 1

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Renal Impairment
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Impaired renal function, defined as eGFR < 20 mL/min/1.73 m2 (CKD-EPI) or requiring dialysis, as determined at Visit 1

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Haemoglobin
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Haemoglobin (HgB) <9 g/dl at Visit 1

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Ketoacidosis History
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: History of ketoacidosis

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Major Surgery
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Major surgery (major according to the investigator’s assessment) performed within 90 days prior to Visit 1, or scheduled major elective surgery (e.g. hip replacement) within 90 days after Visit 1

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Gastrointestinal Disorders
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Gastrointestinal surgery or gastrointestinal disorder that could interfere with trial medication absorption in the investigator’s opinion

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Malignancy
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Any documented active or suspected malignancy or history of malignancy within 2 years prior to screening, except appropriately treated basal cell carcinoma of the skin, in situ carcinoma of uterine cervix, or low risk prostate cancer
